# üèõÔ∏è AI Museum Curator ‚Äî Greek Mythology Edition

Interactive Streamlit app that combines the MET Museum Open API with OpenAI to provide curator-style interpretations of artworks and a hands-on interactive zone for users.

---

## ‚úÖ Key features

- Select a Greek god/hero/creature and read a short fixed bio (optionally expand via AI).  
- Fetch related artworks from the MET Museum and browse thumbnails.  
- View high-resolution images and AI-generated curator analyses.  
- Interactive Art Zone:
  - Detail & Symbolism (ask about visual details)
  - Style Analyzer (upload a sketch/photo and get style hints)
  - Myth Identifier (one-sentence description ‚Üí AI identifies likely deity and fetches artworks)
  - Which Greek Deity Are You? (short personality quiz ‚Üí AI maps to a deity and suggests artworks)

---

## üîí OpenAI API Key

To enable AI features, provide an OpenAI API key either as an environment variable `OPENAI_API_KEY` or by entering your key in the Home page input box (stored only in your session). The app will not save your key on a server.

---

## üß≠ How to Use (Step-by-step)

1. Run the app (local) or open the deployed URL.  
2. On **Home**, enter your OpenAI API key to enable AI functions.  
3. Go to **Greek Deities**: pick a figure ‚Üí click **Expand description with AI** (optional) ‚Üí click **Fetch related works**.  
4. Go to **Works & Analysis**: browse thumbnails ‚Üí select an artwork ‚Üí click **Generate AI Curatorial Analysis**.  
5. Visit **Interactive Art Zone** for deeper interactions:
   - Describe a scene ‚Üí AI will identify the most likely deity and fetch related works.  
   - Take the personality quiz to discover your mythic match and see recommended works.  
   - Upload sketches to get style-matching feedback.  
   - Ask about a visual detail to get curator-style explanation.

---

